## Initial Setup

### 1. Build and deploy the worker bundle

{% if "web-user-app" in platforms %}
```bash
cd web-user-app
npm install
npm run build:cloudflare
npx wrangler deploy
```
{% endif %}

{% if "web-admin-portal" in platforms %}
```bash
cd web-admin-portal
npm install
npm run build:cloudflare
npx wrangler deploy
```
{% endif %}

### 2. Set Environment Variables

In Cloudflare dashboard -> Workers & Pages -> your worker -> Settings -> Variables:

| Variable | Value |
|----------|-------|
| `NEXT_PUBLIC_API_BASE_URL` | `https://api.{{ project_slug }}.com` |
| `AUTH_SECRET` | Generated secret for NextAuth |

## CI/CD

GitHub Actions deploys on push to `main`:
- Builds the OpenNext Cloudflare bundle
- Deploys the worker via Wrangler

## Required GitHub Secrets

| Secret | Description |
|--------|-------------|
| `CLOUDFLARE_ACCOUNT_ID` | Cloudflare account ID |
| `CLOUDFLARE_API_TOKEN` | API token with Workers edit permissions |
